---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SectionLabel from "../components/SectionLabel.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="About Jerry Chen — computer science at McGill, working across SWE, AI, and NLP research."
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl">About</h1>

  <section class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-6 sm:flex-row sm:items-start sm:gap-8">
    <figure
      class="shrink-0 overflow-hidden border border-border bg-surface"
      style="width: 180px; aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;"
    >
      <img
        src="/images/jerry.jpg"
        alt="Jerry Chen"
        width="180"
        height="225"
        class="h-full w-full object-cover"
      />
    </figure>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p>
        I'm Jerry Chen — an undergraduate B.Sc. Honours Computer Science
        student (minor in Statistics) at McGill University. I'm currently
        figuring out where I want to put my time, somewhere between SWE and AI
        internships, startup ideas, and NLP research.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of work, I've played soccer since I was 8 years old and recently 
        started playing competitively again for Inter Montreal. Besides soccer, 
        I'm very into fashion, sustainability, and eating amazing foods.
      </p>
      <p>
        I built this website as a place for me to journal my achievements outside of th LinkedIn bubble.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-12">
    <SectionLabel>What I work on</SectionLabel>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p>
        My work spans three loose tracks. 
        <strong>Software engineering</strong>{" "}
        — typical full-stack and systems projects, including internships at RBC and InterPro Steel,
        as well as my Canadian University sports fantasy platform.{" "}
        <strong>AI development</strong> — building with LLMs and implementing AI features,
        including two very cool hackathon projects.{" "}
        <strong>NLP research</strong> — a more academic approach focusing on how LLMs work,
        exploring token uncertainty and potential methods of pruning uncertain outputs. 
      </p>
      <p>
        Projects on this site are tagged
        <a href="/projects?tag=swe">SWE</a>,
        <a href="/projects?tag=ai">AI</a>,
        <a href="/projects?tag=ai">NLP</a>, or
        <a href="/projects?tag=nlp">School</a> so you can filter to the track you
        care about.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

    <style>
      .icon-link {
        display: inline-flex;
        color: var(--muted);
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: color 0.12s ease;
      }
      .icon-link:hover {
        color: var(--accent);
      }
    </style>
  </section>
</Layout>
